		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi, the rates listed in the APU DMC page are CPU cycles:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_DMC">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_DMC</a><!-- m --><br /><br />And the APU page says DMC timer runs every two CPU cycles:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU</a><!-- m --><br /><br />So I need to divide the rate by 2 before loading the timer, is that correct?<br /><br />Thanks.

		

